  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a particle moving horizontally to the right into a region between two parallel horizontal charged plates. The upper plate has a positive charge, and the lower plate has a negative charge.\" src=\"/images/a74981734a810d07a316a38c792702fe.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A particle with charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive q\"><math alttext=\"positive q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi></math></span></span> moves horizontally with speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v \"><math alttext=\"v \" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>v</mi></math></span></span> into the region between two parallel horizontal charged plates. The upper plate has a uniformly distributed positive charge and the lower plate has a uniformly distributed negative charge of the same magnitude. A magnetic field <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B sub 1 \"><math alttext=\"B sub 1 \" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> is introduced into the region between the plates such that the particle moves through the region between the plates with no change to its velocity. In a second scenario, a second particle with charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative q \"><math alttext=\"negative q \" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>-</mo><mi>q</mi></math></span></span> and a smaller mass than the first particle moves horizontally with speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v \"><math alttext=\"v \" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>v</mi></math></span></span> into the same region between the plates. A magnetic field <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B sub 2\"><math alttext=\"B sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> is introduced into the region between the plates such that the second particle also moves through the region between the plates with no change to its velocity. Which of the following correctly compares the magnitude and direction of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B sub 1\"><math alttext=\"B sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B sub 2\"><math alttext=\"B sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>?</p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup align:center cols:3 colsep:0 frame:none rowsep:0\"><colgroup><col class=\"colspec colname:col1 colnum:1 colsep:1\"></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row rowsep:1\"><th class=\"entry colname:col1\"></th><th class=\"entry colname:col2\">Magnitudes</th><th class=\"entry colname:col3\">Directions of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B sub 1\"><math alttext=\"B sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B sub 2\"><math alttext=\"B sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span></th></tr></thead><tbody class=\"tbody\"><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">A</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B sub 1 is greater than B sub 2\"><math alttext=\"B sub 1 is greater than B sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span></td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Same direction</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">B</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B sub 1 is greater than B sub 2\"><math alttext=\"B sub 1 is greater than B sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span></td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Opposite directions</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">C</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B sub 1 equals B sub 2\"><math alttext=\"B sub 1 equals B sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span></td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Same direction</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">D</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B sub 1 equals B sub 2\"><math alttext=\"B sub 1 equals B sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span></td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Opposite directions</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n",
